{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":15703,"duration_api_ms":15601,"num_turns":5,"result":"Here's the complete token flow:\n\n### Generation\n- **`src/main/java/com/acme/auth/TokenManager.java:7`** — `generate(String username)`: Creates a token string. Called during authentication.\n- **`src/main/java/com/acme/auth/AuthService.java:15`** — `authenticate()` calls `tokenManager.generate(username)` and stores the token in `SessionStore`.\n\n### Validation\n- **`src/main/java/com/acme/auth/TokenManager.java:12`** — `validate(String token)`: Checks non-null and prefix.\n- **`src/main/java/com/acme/auth/AuthService.java:25`** — `validateToken(String token)`: Delegates to `TokenManager.validate()`.\n- **`src/main/java/com/acme/user/UserController.java:14,21,30,38`** — Every endpoint (`listUsers`, `getUser`, `createUser`, `deleteUser`) calls `authService.validateToken(token)` as a guard.\n\n### Refresh\n- **`src/main/java/com/acme/auth/TokenManager.java:17`** — `refresh(String oldToken)`: Extracts the username via `extractUsername()` (line 22) and calls `generate()` to issue a new token. Note: the comment says it \"must invalidate old token first\" but the code doesn't actually do that.\n\n### Session Invalidation\n- **`src/main/java/com/acme/auth/AuthService.java:21`** — `logout(String username)`: Calls `sessionStore.invalidate(username)`.\n\nThree files total, all under `com.acme.auth` and `com.acme.user`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ee883ea4-9e0a-482b-9c79-50e46b5955a7","total_cost_usd":0.08712475,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7337,"cache_read_input_tokens":45037,"output_tokens":749,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7337,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":5,"outputTokens":749,"cacheReadInputTokens":4